            <title>[HBASE-5768] Question about configuring HBase file size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5768</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;My use-case: I have several HBase tables in which entries are pushed constantly(300k entries/5min,6-7Gb/day). I started with tables splitted in 32 regions.&lt;br/&gt;
File size is currently set to 1Gb. I&apos;m using this tables to perfom real-time scans via a web app. &lt;br/&gt;
Problem: Sometimes,but pretty frequently tables are frozen and I get scanner timeout exception.I found in logs that many splits and compactions are performing and I think this are the cause. If I stop pushing data into tables, are scans are running ok.&lt;br/&gt;
Could you provide me some advices to do in order to avoid this problem?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
